# Advantage and Disadvantage

Not all situations are equal. Fighting downhill against an enemy who can't see you creates favorable circumstances. Attempting to pick a lock while hanging from a rope in the rain creates unfavorable ones. Advantage and disadvantage represent these situational modifiers—the tactical edges and setbacks that emerge from circumstances rather than innate capability.

Autumn Phoenix RPG uses simple +1/-1 modifiers rather than complex advantage mechanics. When circumstances favor you, add +1 to your roll. When they work against you, subtract 1. These bonuses and penalties stack with your attributes and skills, creating meaningful tactical decisions without overwhelming complexity.

