## Playing with Advantage and Disadvantage

### Creating Advantages

Smart players create advantages through tactical play:

**Combat:** Position yourself on higher ground before fighting. Coordinate with allies for flanking. Use smoke bombs or darkness to blind enemies while you navigate by sound.

**Skills:** Gather tools before attempting difficult tasks. Research topics before knowledge checks. Create favorable conditions (good light, quiet environment, no time pressure) before crucial attempts.

**Preparation:** Scout ahead to identify advantageous positions. Prepare backup plans that create advantages when primary plans fail. Invest in equipment that grants advantage (proper tools, quality gear).

### Avoiding Disadvantages

Disadvantages often come from poor planning or bad luck, but can be avoided:

**Combat:** Don't fight prone unless forced to. Maintain awareness to avoid being surprised. Keep equipment in good repair to avoid penalties from damaged gear.

**Skills:** Carry proper tools for tasks you attempt frequently. Don't rush unless necessary—time pressure is a common source of disadvantage. Work in favorable conditions when possible.

**Contingency:** Plan for worst-case scenarios. Carry backup equipment. Develop skills that mitigate common disadvantages (darkvision negates darkness penalties, high Athletics reduces difficult terrain penalties).

